Last week the  state capture commission led by chief justice Raymond Zondo delivered  part 4 of its report. In this episode of  Sunday Times Politics Weekly we reflect on the outcomes of the commission’s work and whether SA is a better place after its revelations. Join the debate: Joining us for that conversation are political journalist Mawande AmaShabalala, associate professor at the School of Governance at Wits University William Gumede and senior associate in forensics at ENSAfrica Adrian Roux. For more episodes, click here. Subscribe for free episodes: iono.fm | Spotify | Apple Podcast | Pocket Casts | Player.fm Support independent journalism by subscribing to the Sunday Times. Just R20 for the first month.